{"cursor":"41691","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"\n{{Infobox sport |name = |image = Powder_turn.jpg |imagesize = 250px |caption = A\nsnowboarder making a turn in fresh snow. |union = |nickname = |first = 1960s,\nUnited States |registered = |clubs = |contact = |team = |mgender = |category =\nOutdoor |equipment = Snowboard deck, bindings, boots |venue = |obsolete =\n|olympic = 1998 }} 'Snowboarding' is a winter sport that involves descending a\nslope that is covered with snow while standing on a board attached to a rider's\nfeet, using a special boot set onto a mounted binding. The development of\nsnowboarding was inspired by skateboarding, sledding, surfing and skiing. It was\ndeveloped in the United States in the 1960s and became a Winter Olympic Sport in\n1998. In 2002 competitive snowboarders formed the World Snowboard Tour.\n","linknr":653,"url":"Snowboarding","recorded":1362372125,"links":83,"instances":["snowboard_games","hawaii"],"pdf":["http://exchanges.state.gov/englishteaching/forum/archives/docs/10-48-1-f.pdf"],"categories":["American inventions","Olympic sports","Snowboarding|","Winter sports"],"headings":["History","Styles","Safety and precautions","Competition","Well-known events","Subculture","Media","See also","References","External links"],"image":["//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/ca/Powder_turn.jpg/250px-Powder_turn.jpg","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/5/51/USMintSnowboardUtahQuarterDesign.jpg","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/magnify-clip.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/2/2c/Squaw3.jpg/220px-Squaw3.jpg","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/magnify-clip.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/23/Snowboarder_in_the_trees.jpg/220px-Snowboarder_in_the_trees.jpg","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/magnify-clip.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/f/f2/Edit-clear.svg/40px-Edit-clear.svg.png","//upload